Input: {
  "file_path": "/Volumes/Development/booked/helix/.worktrees/feature-phase-2-component-build-helixtailwind/packages/tailwind-preset/README.md",
  "content": "# @helixds/tailwind-preset\n\nTailwind CSS preset that maps [Helix design tokens](../hx-tokens/README.md) to Tailwind utility classes.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nnpm install @helixds/tailwind-preset\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```js\n// tailwind.config.js\nimport helixPreset from '@helixds/tailwind-preset';\n\nexport default {\n  presets: [helixPreset],\n  content: ['./src/**/*.{html,js,ts,jsx,tsx}'],\n};\n```\n\nThen load the Helix token CSS in your entry file (required for CSS custom properties to resolve):\n\n```css\n/* main.css */\n@import '@helix/tokens/tokens.css';\n@tailwind base;\n@tailwind components;\n@tailwind utilities;\n```\n\n## What's Included\n\n### Colors\n\nAll Helix color palettes are available as Tailwind color utilities:\n\n```html\n<!-- Brand palettes (50–950 shades) -->\n<div class=\"bg-primary-500 text-primary-50\">Primary</div>\n<div class=\"bg-secondary-500\">Secondary</div>\n<div class=\"bg-accent-500\">Accent</div>\n<div class=\"bg-neutral-100\">Neutral</div>\n<div class=\"bg-success-500\">Success</div>\n<div class=\"bg-warning-400\">Warning</div>\n<div class=\"bg-error-500\">Error</div>\n<div class=\"bg-info-500\">Info</div>\n\n<!-- Semantic colors -->\n<div class=\"bg-surface text-text\">Default surface</div>\n<div class=\"bg-surface-raised\">Raised card</div>\n<p class=\"text-text-secondary\">Muted text</p>\n<div class=\"border border-border\">Bordered</div>\n```\n\n### Spacing\n\nSpacing utilities map to `--hx-space-*` tokens:\n\n```html\n<div class=\"p-4 gap-6 m-8\">...</div>\n```\n\n### Typography\n\nFont family, size, weight, and line height map to `--hx-font-*` tokens:\n\n```html\n<p class=\"font-sans text-md font-normal leading-normal\">Body text</p>\n<h1 class=\"font-sans text-4xl font-bold leading-tight\">Heading</h1>\n<code class=\"font-mono text-sm\">Code</code>\n```\n\n### Shadows\n\n```html\n<div class=\"shadow-sm\">Small shadow</div>\n<div class=\"shadow-md\">Medium shadow</div>\n<div class=\"shadow-lg\">Large shadow</div>\n```\n\n## Dark Mode\n\nDark mode is activated via the `data-theme=\"dark\"` attribute on a parent element:\n\n```html\n<!-- Light mode (default) -->\n<body>\n  <div class=\"bg-surface text-text\">Light content</div>\n</body>\n\n<!-- Dark mode -->\n<body data-theme=\"dark\">\n  <div class=\"bg-surface text-text\">Dark content (tokens auto-switch)</div>\n</body>\n```\n\nSince colors reference CSS custom properties, dark mode token overrides\n(defined in `@helix/tokens`) apply automatically — no Tailwind `dark:` variant\nneeded for semantic colors.\n\nFor non-semantic utilities, use the `dark:` variant as usual:\n\n```html\n<div class=\"bg-white dark:bg-neutral-900\">Manual dark override</div>\n```\n\n## How It Works\n\nThe preset maps Helix CSS custom properties (`--hx-color-primary-500`, etc.)\nto Tailwind's theme values using `var()` references. This means:\n\n1. Values are resolved at runtime from the loaded CSS variables\n2. Dark mode works automatically via `data-theme=\"dark\"` and CSS overrides\n3. Consumer apps can override tokens by redefining `--hx-*` variables\n\n```css\n/* Override a token */\n:root {\n  --hx-color-primary-500: #7c3aed; /* Custom purple */\n}\n```\n\nAll Tailwind utilities that use `primary-500` will automatically reflect the\noverride without any config change.\n"
}

